The bug in this code is that you are resetting the value of 'total' inside 
the loop causing it to always contain the amount of the last item. To fix i
it, move the line "var total = 0;" outside the loop so it only runs once be
before the start of each iteration. Also, if you want to accumulate totals 
correctly across all iterations, keep the initialization of 'total' inside 
the loop and directly add amounts in the following line:

```tundra
val items = [
  { amount: 2 },
  { amount: 5 },
  { amount: 7 }
];

var total = 0;
for (item in items) {
  total = total + item.amount;
}

print(total);
```
